rComments: This prof was by far one of my favorites. She is extremely straight forward her lectures are quick and concise. Would definitely take this prof again.

Having Prof. Samuel teaching SOC275 was a pleasure. She has 3 test @ 25% each and an annotated bibliography @ 25%. TA's provided good feedback on the assignment and students did well on both tests and the assignment. Make sure to read the textbook - this is essential for your success in the course. Overall, good prof and lecture's were detailed.

SOC263, 3 non-cumulative tests - 25% each, 1 assignment - 25%. No exam. Her tests are all MCQ and T/F - some of the wrong choices don't relate to the topic at all, so the question are super straight forward. She is also very inspirational and has great passion teaching sociology. This is coming from a guy who doesn't major or minor in sociology

Only had three tests (two worth 25% and one 50%), always let class out early, tests in class have multple choices and an essay portion, lots of reading, often in class has a very pessimistic attitude and often repets stuff from soc263 but still enjoyable class
